🔧 Syntax

=XLOOKUP(lookup_value, lookup_array, return_array)


---

🧠 Deep Meaning

lookup_value

👉 Value to search


---

lookup_array

👉 Where to search


---

return_array

👉 What to return


---

🧠 Execution Example

=XLOOKUP(1, F2:F3, G2:G3)

Steps:

1. Search 1 in F column


2. Find row


3. Return from G column




---

🔥 Advanced Features


---

✅ 1. Works both directions

👉 Can lookup left or right


---

✅ 2. No column index needed

👉 More stable


---

✅ 3. Handles errors

