🧠 PART 2: LEFT LOOKUP PROBLEM


---

❓ Q2: Why is VLOOKUP failing here?

🧾 Sheet

E (name)	F (customer_id)

Vinod	1
Ravi	2



---

Requirement: 👉 Use customer_id → get name


---

❌ Wrong Attempt

=VLOOKUP(1, E2:F3, 1, FALSE)


---

❌ Problem

👉 Lookup column is NOT first
👉 VLOOKUP can’t go right → left


---

✅ Answer

> VLOOKUP cannot perform left lookup. The lookup column must be the first column in the table.




---

✔ Fix

=XLOOKUP(1, F2:F3, E2:E3)


---


---

🧠 PART 3: APPROX MATCH TRAP


---

❓ Q3: Why wrong results?

=VLOOKUP(5, A2:B5, 2, TRUE)


---

❌ Problem

👉 TRUE = approximate match
👉 If data not sorted → wrong result


---

✅ Answer

> Using TRUE performs approximate matching and requires sorted data. If the data is not sorted, it can return incorrect results.




---

✔ Fix

=VLOOKUP(5, A2:B5, 2, FALSE)


